From b72b9cf71932a2306e2cebcad3ccd59437cf02a5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: moe-flash <moe-flash@localhost>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 23:18:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 01/12] moe-flash: add eval callback for expert routing
 interception

Add llama-moe-flash module that installs an eval callback to intercept
ffn_moe_topk tensors after argsort. Supports three modes:

- Routing logging (LLAMA_FLASH_MOE_LOG_ROUTING=1): logs selected expert
  IDs per layer to stderr
- posix_fadvise prefetch (LLAMA_FLASH_MOE_FADVISE=1): issues WILLNEED
  hints for next layer's expert files
- (future) io_uring reads into staging buffers

On UMA systems (Strix Halo), the tensor readback is a simple memcpy
since Vulkan buffers are host-visible and host-coherent.

Controlled by LLAMA_FLASH_MOE_ENABLED=1 env var.
