Subject: [PATCH 04/12] moe-flash: add io_uring expert reads with staging
 buffers

Add io_uring-based async read path for MoE expert weights. When enabled
with LLAMA_FLASH_MOE_IOURING=1 and built with -DGGML_IOURING=ON:

- Allocates 2MB-aligned staging buffers (one per top-k expert slot)
- Registers buffers with io_uring for zero-copy fixed reads
- Tries SQPOLL mode for kernel-side submission (falls back to normal)
- Submits reads when routing decision is intercepted
- Waits for completion before next layer's routing
- Reports timing stats (submit/wait latency, bytes read)

The io_uring path supersedes posix_fadvise when both are available.
Staging buffers are the foundation for Phase 3 (Vulkan integration).
