From 6cdcb2cd0b3d9d04188684082d4ab989e2f1577e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: moe-flash <moe-flash@localhost>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 01:43:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 06/12] moe-flash: add GGUF page cache warming mode (Phase 3)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

New mode that reads expert data directly from the GGUF file at the
known tensor offsets, using io_uring. The reads go into staging buffers
(discarded), but the side effect is that the kernel populates the page
cache for those GGUF regions. When the mmap'd tensor is subsequently
accessed by the Vulkan compute graph, the data is already resident.

This approach requires zero Vulkan changes — the existing mmap-based
tensor access works unchanged, just without page faults.

Enabled with:
  LLAMA_FLASH_MOE_GGUF_PATH=/path/to/model.gguf

Includes a minimal GGUF header parser that extracts expert tensor
offsets and strides (gate, up, down per layer per expert).

Tested on glm-4-7-flash: 64 MB staging, 12 GB read, 368µs avg wait.
---
 src/llama-moe-flash.cpp | 353 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 333 insertions(+), 20 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/llama-moe-flash.cpp b/src/llama-moe-flash.cpp
