Subject: [PATCH 11/12] ggml-vulkan: add GTT size check and fallback for
 buffer_from_host_ptr

On UMA systems, imported host memory counts against the GTT limit.
If the mmap region exceeds available device memory (with headroom),
skip the import and fall back to the regular alloc+copy path.

Also adds a fallback in the model loader: if buffer_from_host_ptr
returns null, fall through to the standard allocation path instead
of throwing an exception.

This allows:
- Small models: zero-copy import via buffer_from_host_ptr (fast)
- Large models with --cpu-moe: experts on CPU (no import), non-expert
  tensors fall back to alloc+copy if import fails
---
